Articulation Agreement Overview

This agreement outlines lower-division course requirements specific to the major. Students are strongly encouraged to consult an academic advisor to ensure they meet all degree requirements for their intended baccalaureate program.


Helpful Resources:

  • CSUB Catalog
  • Transfer Admission Requirements
  • Academic Advising Student Centers
  • CSUB Program Pathways Mapper


Course Equivalency Information for 4-Year Institutions

Students and staff can explore course transfer equivalencies through the Transfer Evaluation System (TES). Equivalency agreements are updated regularly and subject to change. For the most current information, please refer to TES or contact the Articulation Office.

Studying in the Department of English leads to an understanding and appreciation of British, American, and other literature in English, and of the English language, its aesthetic and functional properties, its uses, and the methods by which impressions and ideas are articulated and communicated. The BA in English emphasizes an in-depth study of the nature of the English language, the British, American, and other literary traditions, creative writing, and critical approaches to literature.


The department also offers a minor in English Literature, a minor in Linguistics, and a minor in Children’s Literature. In addition, the department has two post-baccalaureate certificates, in Writing and in Children’s Literature.


For additional information, visit the the following:

Department of English
